terful translation by Craig Williamson.Accompanied by an introduction by noted medievalist Tom Shippey on the literary scope and vision of these timeless poems and Williamson's own introductions to the individual works and his essay on translating Old English poetry, the texts transport us back to the medieval scriptorium or ancient mead-hall, to share a herdsman's recounting of the story of the world's creation or a people's sorrow at the death of a beloved king, to be present at the clash of battle or to puzzle over the sacred and profane answers to riddles posed over a thousand years ago. This is poetry as stunning in its vitality as it is true to its sources. Were Williamson's idiom not so modern, we might think that the Anglo-Saxon poets had taken up the lyre again and begun to sing once more.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 16. Mai 2019) 0aDidactic poetry, EnglishvTranslations into English. 0aEnglish poetryyOld English, ca. 450-1100vTranslations into English. 0aEpic poetry, EnglishvTranslations into English. 0aRiddlesvTranslations into English. 4aCultural Studies. 4aLiterature. 4aMedieval and Renaissance Studies. 4aPoetry. 70(DE-601)1041377890(DE-588)4036774-5aLyrik2gnd 70(DE-601)1041378940(DE-588)4015065-3aEpos2gnd 70(DE-601)1058366990(DE-588)4112501-0aAltenglisch2gnd 7aLITERARY COLLECTIONS / English, Irish, Scottish, Welsh.2bisacsh1 aShippey, Tom.1 aWilliamson, Craig.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017z978311062526408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Studies 2017z9783110548198oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn Press eBook Package 2017z978311055030